'''PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi Tbk''' (commonly known as '''Emtek''') is an Indonesian [[technology company|technology]], [[telecommunications industry|telecommunication]] and [[mass media|media]] conglomerate and headquartered in [[Jakarta]]. As of 2013, it is Indonesia’s second largest media company.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://investing.businessweek.com/research/markets/news/article.asp?docKey=600-201305070001MERGENT_AU_NEWSB_070513192938327502954-1 | title = PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi trading at low volume | date = 5 July 2013 | publisher = Bloomberg Businessweek }}</ref> It is the parent company for subsidiaries which include terrestrial television subscription NexMedia and three television stations – [[SCTV (Indonesia)|SCTV]], [[Indosiar]] and [[O Channel]]. It was established in 1983 by Eddy K. Sariaatmadja. Currently, the company is headed by Alvin W. Sariaatmadja as its [[President (corporate title)|President Director]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.emtek.co.id/management/board-of-directors?locale=en_US |title=Board of Directors |publisher=Emtek |accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref>

== History ==
In 1997, PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi Komputer evolved to PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi Indonesia.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.emtek.co.id/files/uploads/report/file/2016/May/25/57449dfdaf3d8/emtek-laporan-tahunan-2012-penyajian-kembali-7.pdf |title=PT ELANG MAHKOTA TEKNOLOGI Tbk Annual Report 2012 |publisher=Emtek}}</ref>
On 2 August 2004, the company established a local television station – O Channel, along with the MRA Media Group. In 2007, Emtek took full control of the station. In 2008, the group took control of Surya Citra Media (SCTV). In November 2011, Emtek launched a subscription TV channel, named NexMedia. Emtek as an Official Broadcaster of the [[2018 Asian Games]] for the [[Indonesian Olympic Committee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bola.com/asian-games/read/3218458/video-emtek-sebagai-official-broadcaster-asian-games-2018 |website= Bola.com |title=VIDEO: Emtek Sebagai Official Broadcaster Asian Games 2018! |date=January 8, 2018}}</ref>

